Commentary Text: Hasaranga to Pollard, out Lbw!! More wreckage. And This time it's their biggest piece in the possible resurrection who's going back for a golden duck -- and he's going back because he's misread the googly big time, and has shuffles across in his crease to defend down the wrong line entirely. Commentary Text: Brevis to Kohli, out Lbw!! First ball in IPL from Brevis and he might've dismissed Kohli here. It's been given out LBW, but Kohli has reviewed it. And here's why - there's an inside edge onto pad. The bat is not that far in front of pad, so the third umpire wants to be absolutely sure that it has hit the bat first. Oh wait, now this is controversial. He feels that it has bat and pad simultaneously, so not enough evidence to overturn, and Kohli is furious. Wow. Length ball sliding through on middle, looked like an inside edge onto pad. But the third umpire feels he doesn't have conclusive proof. Don't think it's going to have an impact on the result thankfully. Kohli lbw b Brevis 48(36) [4s-5]

Commentary Text: Unadkat to Kohli, out Anuj Rawat Run Out!! 1 run completed. A direct hit from the fielder running in from deep midwicket! MI look confident. Oh Rawat's bat is on the line! Superb work from Ramandeep to offer just a glimmer of hope for MI. This is back of a length on off, a slower one that Kohli tucks gently through the vacant midwicket region. Call is for two and Rawat pushes hard, but is beaten by this flat throw from Ramandeep who made good ground running in off the rope. Anuj Rawat run out (Ramandeep Singh ) 66(47) [4s-2 6s-6]
